author: Seattle Times staff
title: Man wounded in drive-by shooting in Seattle’s Central District
text:
A man was wounded early Tuesday morning in an apparent drive-by shooting in the Central District, Seattle police said.
Police responded to reports of gunfire at 23rd Avenue and East Cherry Street just before 2 a.m. and found the victim in the parking lot of a gas station. The 48-year-old victim said someone had opened fire from a passing vehicle, striking him in the arm and grazing his abdomen.
The wounded man was taken to Harborview Medical Center with what police called non-life-threatening injuries.
Officers spoke with several witnesses who were unable to provide any details about the shooting.
